{
  "stem": "2435.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I was able to attend a kindergarten school for one year, which was the so-called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And after one year, I was told I could not work there anymore.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a one and a half year training.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because they told me as a non-Aryan, I had to leave the kindergarten school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And here, again, I had all my friends who stayed with me and kept with me and were wonderful when they heard that I was non-Aryan.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was no-- never talk about it before.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was very unhappy, not knowing-- I wanted to work with children and babies.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I found a infants and babies clinic in Wannsee, which was a private clinic owned by a Jew.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this was a training of a one year.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I can never forget that one morning-- and I was only with Christian girls.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was the only non-Christian girl.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I'll never forget that one morning somebody knocked very wildly at the door of this clinic.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And two Gestapo men were demanding to have the door open.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the owner opened the door.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They threw him down on the floor and beat him terribly.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We all saw that, when they beat him up.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he was carried out then to the truck, which they had outside.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we heard later on that he was deported to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "His name was Fockenheim.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was 1937.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in spite of the screams and tears of his wife, who wanted to run after him, they didn't pay any attention.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a horrible experience.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I thought, well, this is the end of me, and they will take me out of-- but no.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
